---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 207
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Death=‘Die Before Ye Die'
By: Sri Ramana Maharshi
---
\'What if anyone is dead? What if any one is ruined? Be dead
yourself—be ruined yourself.’ In that sense there is no pain after
one’s death. What is meant by this sort of death? Annihilation of the
ego, though the body is alive.
